inn1.comm: starts with a tidy enough delivery, shooting past the left hander's edge
nips away off the seam, rising, and is left outside off
overstretched down the channel, and wide is the obvious call
straighter delivery this time, back on the good line down off - decent length, too
the best delivery of the over so far, Gayle in two minds about how to play one which shuffles past him; he plays late and the ball shoots through
an early decision to leave that one
fuller delivery, outside off and that pips the previous delivery, with some movement away from the batsman he prompts Gayle to play and miss
down leg - and Gnasher wins a biscuit
outside off, and cut straight to the man at point
oh dear, another wide - down leg again
too full but let's take nothing away from a lovely front-foot drive through long-off
straight, better delivery, defended on the back foot
straight again, sharp and has the batsman bending over in defence, nearly cutting him in two
overpitched this time and yet another drive, through cover this time, merely leaning into that off the back foot to time it all the way to the boundary
dinked down off the back foot for a shuffle-and-run, which bags the strike, too
on off-and-middle, squeezed into midwicket
there goes Smith with another one of those well-timed drives - that one was full and he steps forward to time through long-off
gone this time, though - trying to drive, but skewing an outside edge to backward point, Bell snapping up low, to his right. A good catch
yorker outside off greets him and Chanderpaul responds with a late defence
outside off, rising on its way through to Prior. Good-looking delivery, but Chanderpaul isn't tempted
a rare sign of swing but wide enough to leave outside off
shapes across the left hander, who leaves
tighter, nice, but Gayle is confident in leaving
Plunkett still struggling with his length, too full again, and Gayle presses through cover to get off the mark
left alone down the channel
ooh, a drive is dropped by Cook at extra cover - it flew
left alone outside off
pressed forward for a single
straight ball rising, squares him up but he manages to prod down off the back foot to point
full, driven through cover
testing one, pitching on off and moving away from the righthander on a good length
the batsman's forced to think about it again, but judges the leave well
outside off, full, and a well-struck drive to cover, but straight at the man
left alone on the rise outside off
shoots through on a good length, the ball rises fairly sharply
comes forward and an "Oh" as Chanderpaul comes forward, misses, and is rapped high, too high in fact for a shout
down leg, and Plunkett's not happy with himself
outside off, tries to turn the face and a thick outside edge flies just short of second slip - it's Cook again, but this time there was no catch on offer
fuller and well driven through extra cover
straight and tries to brandish a thick clip off the hips, but mistimes it and the ball falls down, lifeless
round the wicket, up there, defended down on the front foot
down the channel, fairly innocuous
pushed right up there, defended down with ease
full, wide, Chanderpaul tempted into the drive, but misses completely - Prior tidies up with a dive
turned round through fine leg
left alone down off
on off, driven to mid-off, logically enough
not full enough to pull as Chanderpaul would have liked, so it skews off towards Panesar who runs round from mid-on
full ball, encouraging the drive... and Chanderpaul obliges with a firm off-drive
on leg, played off the legs to deep backward square leg
outside off, just down the channel, left alone
short and smashed through the off-side now
outside off, left alone
on middle, knocked down off the hips to short midwicket and they shuffle a single through
left alone on the back foot, the ball sailing down off
outside off, driven off the back foot to just inside the cover boundary
driven into the ground on its way to cover
defended this time
left alone outside off
slinks this one down the channel
played forward on the front foot
pressed off the legs to square and rocketed back in by Pietersen
straight, worked down and thoughts of a shuffle
on off, sharp one has Chanderpaul fending deftly down off the back foot
on off, defended solidly
a pinch of swing, a punch of a forward defensive
on leg, tucked off the hips to square
half-volley, rushes outside off, Gayle decides to play but soon wishes he hadn't - as the ball nips away at the last minute off the seam
dropped by Bell at backward point. Sitter in fact.  Collingwood would have had that one, you'd imagine, but as captain he now fields closer to the action
driven to cover
dribbled forward for a quick single
defended on the front foot this time
cut strongly off the back foot where Bell gets his body right behind it and stops well
on off, driven to mid-off
outside off, dropped a touch short, slapped to the man at cover
on leg, turned to backward square
pushed up there and defended down
driven to mid-on
too full, driven to Broad who throws it back in quite weakly. As a girl, I can't possibly say "Like a girl" because us girls can throw, you know
a big outside edge sprays just wide of a diving first slip
defended on the front foot
left alone outside off
skews down leg
drags down a touch short, very straight, worked into the off side
outside off, crashes down an inside edge
outside off, slashed through cover for a firm four
on leg, tucked with a slight squeeze, through fine leg
a lesser-spotted dot
on leg, worked round very fine but it won't go all the way
pushed up there, defended
comes forward with attacking intent, worked to square
on leg, worked round to wide fine leg
on middle, pops up a leading edge trying to turn to midwicket
on leg, defended forward
outside off, stuns a drive to the covers
left alone outside off
on off, defended forward
on off, turned back in, defended again
opens his shoulders to drive to cover
flighted up, waited, driven to short midwicket
outside off, just past the outside edge - Chanderpaul tempted to cut - and is defeated
outside edge through third man for two
over the wicket to the left hander who prods to the covers
decent delivery, at 70.7mph it's not the quickest, but it was on the button and so defended
not much width outside off, but Gayle does really well to drive through cover to bring up his 6000th ODI run. A good milestone to reach and does so in appropriate style
outside off, a prod-and-run
defended forward
prodded down on the front foot
defended forward
more defending
on the button, good tight stuff, more defending
gives it more air and Gayle flashes out at that one, but the ball flies down in front of gully
worked out to cover for an easy single
worked in front of square
swept thorugh deep square leg
third umpire needed for a quick single where Anderson shied down the stumps - but Chanderpaul was a long way home
outside off, padded up, the ball crept past the pad anyway
defended on the front foot this time
defended on the front foot again
outside off, flashed at
comes forward, works down to fine leg with an easy tickle
good length and bounce, forcing him on to the back foot and looking to work through midwicket
that's weepingly good, Chanderpaul down on his front foot and drilling a straight drive with a rainbow-like parabola way over Panesar's head
defended forward
on middle, turned off the hips to midwicket
outside off, a mistimed cut is missed, Prior takes the ball and lets out an "Ooowayooh" while doing so

outside off and Chanderpaul goes on one knee, trying to scoop it over midwicket. Pietersen inches over, timing his run well, and eventually making it look very easy indeed as he takes a deceptively difficult catch over his shoulder
straight outside off
tucked off the legs square
on leg, defended into the leg-side
outside off, cut down behind point
poked forward for a quick single
on off, worked round through the 45
eased down the corridor
off the mark with a drive to mid-off
pushed up there, a dink-and-run for a single and they had to hurry to make it... in fact, ignore that, he was well home
up there again, the drive to mid-on is mistimed
up there, driven through mid-off
worked to square off the toes
outside off, left alone
up there, but that's driven back through long-on with some very good timing
just to say outside off, Samuels goes chasing that and pays the price as the ball kisses the lip of the bat on the way through to Prior who gratefully accepts
opens up the face and presents it to cover
good yorker, but equally well dug out
outside off, driven to cover and Collingwood does the job
outside off, enough room to cut easily out towards the cover boundary
outside off and gets some accidental lift on that drive towards cover
back of a length, driven for an easy single
outside off, cut out to Anderson at deep point
pushed up there, defended on the front foot, a trapping kind of defence
on leg, brings the bat down late to work it behind square for a quick single, ah, off the pads in fact
bouncer down the corridor, sitting up and saying to the batsman "Smell my cheese"
outside off, and high - wide could be harsh, there
short, poked down defensively to square with a fend of the glove, as it cut back in
outside off, nipped away, left alone
tries the off break, nearly gets the reward, the batsman playing inside it, though
on middle, Gayle defending down into the covers
fast, flat and fired into his off stump, it's defended
blocked out on middle
worked to leg, from just outside the off stump. Marvellous nudge that was
firmly clunked to mid-off
a bit too straight, worked off his legs to Bell at mid-on - just wide of him, in fact
neatly guided out to the off side for another easy end-of-the-over-strike-stealing single
ooh lovely ball, swinging into the left hander who's beaten
clunked out to deep extra cover
dropped him! - a firm push forward outside his off stump, a thin outside edge but Prior couldn't hang on
ooh Morton comes forward, warily so, pushing this to the leg side
beautiful bowling again, drawing Morton into another decidedly fishy waft. He plays and misses
and this rather spits up up Morton, who is playing Mascarenhas as though the bowler has a hand grenade. Maybe he does?
squirted out to the big, vast, African-plain expanse of greenery out to the off side
solidly defended on the front foot
powerfully struck, smacking this over mid-on for four. Cleanly hit
beaten by a touch of turn, the ball takes a thick outside edge
on middle-and-off, Morton sponges it back to Monty
cracked off the back foot
well back in his crease, Gayle pumps this to mid-off
swinging into Gayle's pads who times it to a short midwicket
powerfully cut to Cook on the extra cover boundary, very well timed but Cook does well to save four
"aww, yes" says Prior, as this one darts into Gayle's pads
an absolute rip-snorting jaffacracker! It cut back in massively to Gayle who came forward to defend, the ball darting inside the line - evading the stumps, and Prior
wobbled off his pads. Prior says "oof"
nudged out to cover
another nudge on the front foot, and he's timed it better, allowing him through for a run
ooh he pads this away - don't do that, that be dangerous - but only half a shout from Prior
timed down the ground
defended on the front foot
nicely flighted, drawing Morton forward who defends
cracked off the back foot for a single. But no, Gayle wants two and he'll get it comfortably
swinging into his pads, Gayle defends
cracked square of the wicket. Super cracking

nudged off his hip, Pietersen shies at the stumps but no one's backing up. A terrible throw from Pietersen, to be honest, and all in all a fairly village piece of cricket from England who look half asleep at the moment
bullied down the ground. A front foot bosh, powerfully struck
nudged out to cover
timed out into the covers
ooh well bowled, rapping him on his pads here - though he got an inside edge. And it was outside the leg stump, both factors making my point that it was "well bowled" utterly inaccurate
marvellous delivery, taking the outside edge down to third man
nice and full, Morton drives it down the ground
that's well bowled, swinging into Gayle who clumps it to midwicket
defended on the front foot
swinging away from the right-hander who defends on the front foot. Again
Morton comes forward and defends
squared up by the lightning pace of EhhhhhhhMascarenhas - played it too early
worked out to cover and they pick up two
Gayle climbs into this, pulling it like a loose stray at a nightclub, but can't time it
edged, but through the vacant slips. First slip would've gobbled that up like a hungry fisherman sitting down for his evening meal
nice touch of away swing from Collingwood. Morton pushes it out to cover
punched to mid-off
defended off the back foot
Morton comes forward to defend, dropping it dead and they pick up a very crafty and decidedly sneaking single
Gayle pushes forward to defend
punched off the back foot to extra cover. But straight to extra cover
"awww," says Prior as Morton inside edges this
nice length - and don't even talk to me about the line, which was quite marvellous - outside off stump and Morton can't really time it, clumping it out to cover
left alone outside off
cuts back into Morton who times it out to cover. They scamper a single
neatly turned off his legs
swinging into Gayle who punches it off the back foot to nowhere
an ugly smite over the top - or that was his intent anyway
nudged off his hips
swinging into his pads, Gayle blocks it out
oh lovely shot, a dab outside off down to third man
pushed out to cover
pushed out to cover again but they can't steal a single
short of a length, it's pulled just short of Pietersen at midwicket who makes a complete hash of it
nudged to leg
pushed out to point who fields slickly
turned off his pads for a single down to fine-leg
Gayle tries to crack this off the back foot but can't only pump it back to the bowler
down the leg side, Morton works it to fine leg
straighter this time, Morton works it industrially through midwicket but for a zero
worked to midwicket from outside the off stump
good length from Collingwood, the ball jutting high on Morton's bat - and eventually, after much deliberation and a mini conference, they set for a run
a solid front-foot thump down the ground
dropped down to the leg side for a very well-scampered single
ooh, bit of an inside edge there - Morton not really coming forward sufficiently, but he sets off for two and gets it comfortably
Morton comes forward to defend
well bowled - an excellent yorker. Well dug out by Morton, though
back of a length, Morton defends
he stands tall to this delivery outside the off stump, powerfully driving it up but straight to point
pumped to midwicket but again no run
heavied down the ground, Collingwood gets out of the way - and Monty does brilliantly at long-on, saving four and parrying the ball to Broad who came running in from long-off. Good teamwork
guided to backward point
a good slower-ball on off stump but Morton does well, clamping down on it
ah, neatly dug out from Morton, squeezing it out to long-on
crack: a resounding, faintly beautiful noise of "thwack" as Gayle cuts this but straight to Shah on t'boundary
pushed out to cover
Morton goes for an almighty heave-ho but can only smack it to mid-on
nudged off his pads
short of a length, Morton goes on the pull but ends up getting a taxi home as the ball lands in the outfield like a misfired mortar
carved down to third man
clipped to midwicket - he takes on Pietersen, and wins
that was some smart running for the second
worked off the hips for a quick single
up there, driven to long-on - the crowd loved that, not sure why (beer?), giving Broad almost Panesaral appreciation. But not quite.
flat four, almost taking out the umpire at square leg, who ducked remarkably well
that one was better, up there and defended
hit hard and flat, out of the meat'n'veg of the bat, driven hard through mid-off
a simple caught and bowled for Plunkett, popping up and Plunkett smiles once more
a huge heave from Bravo but he mistimes it to mid-on. That was heading into Ireland if he connected. Or Norway - one of the two
a flourishing flourish out to the off side which goes nowhere. Broad fields
beaten for pace there, the ball wobbling off Bravo's pads
Morton, desperate to crack this out to cover, again mistimes it to nowhere
tries to clump it out to midwicket but can't time it
guided down to third man
it's a four! Wonders will never cease. Down the leg side and flicked down to fine-leg
splodged out to cover and excellent running yields three
ooh well bowled, a little off-cutter from Collingwood but it's very neatly played, just dabbing it out to the off side
guided to point
full, driven out to long-on and they're going for two. Plunkett's the man fielding but throws to the wrong end
hammered for a single to long-on
that is a magnificent stroke from Morton, pulling this through midwicket - he really bullied that. A slap, and a powerful one at that
down on one knee Morton laces this...but straight to cover
far too short again, Morton climbs into it and pulls it for four once more. Immense power
clumped out to midwicket
huge! A vast strike from Morton, stepping to leg before swinging through the line and cracking him over his head for six
a full toss which hurries Morton into a sponge down the wicket, but there's very little jam
clunked to mid-on for a single - no, they're going for two and they'll get it as well. Fantastic running
excellent yorker from Plunkett
a slower ball which he guides to point
an ugly push to leg for another single to the less-than-sharp Bell. He's not been at his slickest today
another drive to Bell, this time deeper at long-on
well, he climbs into this full toss on his legs - as juicy a delivery as he could have wished for - and it's banged over midwicket
but it's too short, drifting down the leg side and it's helped around the corner for four more
pushed out to mid-off; Broad dives and saves four, excellent work. Much more like it
angled down to third man
punched just beyond point
ooh but he plays and misses here, Prior can't take it and they scamper through for a single. England really are under the cosh here; West Indies are running them ragged
pushed down the ground for yet another easy single
full, straight, Bravo tries to scoop this out to point but misses. Clever bowling
but this is not clever - a full toss on his legs. You can guess the result
smacked to mid-on - a real smite, but without timing
ooh a yorker, well bowled, and it very nearly hits the helmet behind Prior, who's been a bit messy today
shot! Fabulous drive, going inside out, over extra cover. Deserved six
carved out to point
hammered out to extra cover for four. No! Shah fields - diving athletically in front of him and saving four with a desperate fling
oh, shot - hit behind square this time, with greater power and that's four
a beamer! That'll be a wide, and West Indies go for a run and very nearly lose a wicket in the process
a slower ball, miles wide of the off stump

a swing and a miss, another wide - and another near-suicidal run from West Indies. But again, they get it! They're having a ball out there - running England ragged, even if the singles they're stealing are far from comfortable
a beautiful flick from Bravo, taking this from off stump and whipping it behind square for four more. Brilliant
cracked on the up but straight to extra cover
swinging into him, it's sponged to leg
clipped out to deep midwicket
a full toss outside the off stump which he pulls down to long-on. Plunkett dives, quite brilliantly, and saves four
squirted out to cover
an almighty heave to long-on - they want three (well, Bravo does) but Morton sends him back
ooh a big, high, full toss which he tries to pull and gets a thick, skying outside edge over cover
flung out over cover
and he drags this onto his stumps - a full delivery which he tries to flay through the covers drags it on

and he's smacked him for four through extra cover. A terrible effort from Alastair Cook out on the boundary who dived over the ball, failing to stop it - and his face rather tells the story for England who have been off the pace today

inn2.comm: starts with one down the channel, left alone
short delivery hustles through around Cook's hip
just outside off, on a length, defended down
short, wide, help yourself... Cook plants a cut high and backward of point
defended on a good line this time
short, straight, rising, fended back down
up there, defended on the front foot
on middle, driven back to the bowler
wide down leg
on off, worked off the hip behind square
on middle, worked to midwicket
across the lefthander, pitches outside off and straightens and there's a waft-and-a-half
pushes him onto the back foot, defended back down
down the off-side channel, Prior, like a proud cockerel, shows his chest off in that huge leave
that's the breakthrough, Prior with a nervous push outside off to a short and wide one; a nothing shot really
tidy, tidy, tidy - rushing that on ethrough on off, the ball bending back out a touch and Bell playing inside it
worked to square and the batsmen decide to "Wait on!"
outside off this time, on a good length, and Bell comes forward to defend on the front foot
on the money, defended forward again
horrible mispull off the base of the bat, did not time that at all
started fairly wide, and went flat and wider - slightly harsh decision, maybe
down the corridor, this time there is a touch of uncertainty, but Cook leaves it well enough alone
short, outside off, and Cook gets hold of it this time, but so does Morton at midwicket - diving out and forward to cut the runs off
up there, defended on the front foot
driven to mid-off who's slightly back, but not quite long-off... Â¾-off perhaps
on off, poked forward
on leg, turned away and the boisterous crowd clap up England's double figures
on leg, knocked into midwicket for a quick single
outside off, poked back down off the back foot to gully
on middle, flicked away with unEnglish wrists through midwicket
bouncer, outside off, a casual sway back is enough evasively speaking
on off, fended into the covers
slower ball, overpitched, guided in front of midwicket with easy timing
hustled up there, a solid defence on the front foot
on off, keeps straight and is left
across off, defended off the back foot
down off, a waft, outside off with a cover drive - missed completely
on leg, clipped away, no need to run for that. No need to even leave the crease
on off, driven forward, looked for the quick single, had to get back quickly
outside off, fended down off the back foot
but that was overpitched, Bell digging that out and turning it off his legs in front of square
a quick single to cover, dink'n'fun fare
Cook stunned the ball to mid-off, there, surprised by the length, which was fuller than expected, and having to adjust at the last minute
a simple, straight drive to mid-off
banged in, but not the wide Bell was expecting as he left it to climb away from him
left alone down off again
slammed in at the batsman, Bell forced to defend on the back foot
the odd appeal for a strangle down the leg-side. Not out, it came off his shirt
that would have been really close, were it not for the inside edge, as the ball came back off the seam (although height would have been a factor, as Hawk-Eye then shows)
good line and length and well defended
another huge appeal for another strangle - Ramdin goes up with delight, but you could tell he wasn't convinced within himself, and indeed it was not out - hitting the shirt
on middle, driven towards midwicket
on off, a touch short, Cook waiting to caress the ball into gully
wide outside off and Cook flays that to backward point where Dwayne Smith takes a great catch, low
Pietersen's immediately forced to pull his head away from that one, swaying away as Powell greets him with a bouncer that flies above Ramdin and on
got him! Pietersen flashes hard and nearly middles an edge, if that makes sense, to second slip. Great catch from Devon Smith, coming from second slip across first, juggles...and then hangs on
up there, defended
straight, defended down off the back foot
defended down
on off-and-middle, Bell looks to wrist that over in front of midwicket, but stops on the shot
on middle, worked through midwicket
poor shot from Shah, the ball rushed down the corridor, the batsman trying to pull that from outside off, and gets nothing on it
good appeal for lbw, rapping him low, but it was going down
on off, worked down to gully
down the channel and Bell 'does a Shah' of the previous over, trying to pull from outside off and playing right over it
outside off, poked down deliberately in front of the slips
short and hooked round and down to long leg
terrific shot, Bell standing tall (relatively) and delivering a beautiful on-drive of pure timing
left alone outside off
on off, the batsman rocking onto his back foot to defend down
good length, on off, Shah standing firm with a defensive
defended on the front foot
short and hooked over the 45
not pulled effectively, straight to square
left alone outside off
short and on off, the batsman can only defend. I say only... he can do what he wants, really, but he does the sensible thing
on leg, guided out to mid-on
down off, rushes through a pull shot - it's still not working, chaps
...he obviously heard me because that was a forceful pull from outside off.
outside off
misfield at mid-off allows an extra run, and the 50 comes up
straight, driven straight to the fielder
outside off, a touch of room, and driven through cover
short and hooked with a Calypsoan down to fine leg
on off, pulled behind square
up there, driven on the toes to mid-on
on leg, lifted well in front of square for a non-negotiable four
dobbled on a length at 76.8mph, Shah just waits to defend down
horrible shot, trying to sweep from outside off and nearly clatters into his stumps
driven to mid-on this time
on off, bounces up and defended back down easily by Shah
outside off, cut easily to point
down leg
waited, and defended with plenty of time on the front foot
on off, worked into midwicket on the rise, just falling short of the man there
played into midwicket again, for an easy single
up there, defended on the back foot
straight up there, defended on the back foot
on middle-and-leg, a good length, worked back down into the leg-side
short, rising, Shah fends back down off the back foot
up there, driven to mid-on
on middle, worked off the front foot and turned right down through the 45
outside off, worked out off the back foot down
tries to lift the ball with his wrists through midwicket
on middle, swivelled round through midwicket
a good length delivery matched with a solid defence
rising bouncer outside off, with a cheeky hint of swing, too, well swayed
straight, on off peg, defended down forward
good-looking delivery again, defended down
outside off, on the back foot, smashed to cover
on middle-and-leg, turned down behind square
outside off, expecting a half-volley but misjudges the length and drives square, getting a thick edge to point for a sharp catch
on middle, up there, worked to cover
top edge, but lands very safe at long leg
outside off, driven to mid-off
on middle, short, and hoisted over and through the 45
an awkward shot, Shah trying to force towards mid-on, but has nowhere near got the room
left alone this time
slung outside off, Collingwood drives into the covers
overstepping, there
straight, short, fended down in front of him
on middle, pitched up, Collingwood drives without much power back to mid-on
good delivery, but good placement, too, Collingwood deliberating going for the up-and-over, sailing over the slips
Collingwood this time squared up at 90.8mph, trying to force the ball through midwicket from outside off, the edge slewing wide past the slips
swing in the air outside off, Shah thinks about playing, then makes the snap decision to pull out - good choice
down the channel, left alone
outside off, eased into the covers
outside off, wide, lifted high and travelling over the ring
on leg, turned round through the 45
on leg again, also to the 45, but with less power - and indeed no bat, just thigh
on off, rising, and guided back down to mid-off
on off, Shah watches and eases the ball into the covers
oops, definitely a wide I'm afraid, down leg
on middle, worked off the hips, tucked in fact, to midwicket
on leg, worked round behind square
straight, popped up, and swiddled back down in front of square
straight, worked down behind square for an easy single
on leg, turned so fine that the keeper was able to stop it
outside off, driven to mid-off
Collingwood waited to guide a wideish one down behind point
beautiful cover drive taken from outside off
pitches on a good length off, a slight arc away from the righthander, and he defends
slightly down leg... but enough
outside off, driven to the cover boundary
outside off, some gentle swing again, defended down
played over that one, trying to find non-existent room to cut, the ball slinking outside off
a quick single this time
driven to mid-on
ducked a bouncer
on leg, turned down to fine
nearly chops that back onto his stumps from outside off - but didn't
stops on the thought of an off-drive, to ease a drive through cover instead
slower delivery, up there, Collingwood defends watchfully
on leg this time, and Collingwood drives easily to midwicket
worked to mid-on
worked into the covers
defended on the back foot
worked off his toes to midwicket
short of a length, Collingwood goes back and punches it to mid-on
and Gayle just gives Shah a touch of room this time, allowing him to flay it through cover
punched through midwicket
pumped down the ground
flicked off his toes down to fine-leg. Excellent running
brilliant! Pumped to Smith's right who dives and saves a run on his follow-through
but it's too full this time, Shah driving him back past him - along the ground this time - for four. Elegant, classy stroke
worked to the right of mid-on without great power
driven out to cover
streaky - very, very streaky. Shah aiming to flick this ball from outside off through midwicket, got a thick leading edge which flew through the vacant slips and down to third man for four
again mistimed over the wicketkeeper's head
down the leg side
on middle-and-leg, Collingwood turns him through midwicket. No great power or intent in the stroke
again drifting down the leg side - Bravo's line is all off at the moment, and his pace too
another gift on his legs for a neatly tucked single
beautifully flicked through midwicket
firmly defended on the front foot. I'm loving that defence
flicked to leg and they'd have been in trouble had mid-on picked it up cleanly
skips down the pitch and picks this up over square leg, falling a few metres ahead of Powell at deep backward square
driven down the ground for a single
nudged to leg
guided out to point, no intent in the stroke
swept to Powell at deep backward square - again it falls just short, and they can only pick up a single
pushed out to cover
ooh - a slower ball which loops onto Shah who defends it...outside his leg stump
a solid and reasonably authoritative drive on the front foot out to long-off, but not really timed
nudged off his legs, Shah sends Collingwood back with a ferociously raucous "nooo"
nudged off his hip for yet another single
stunning on-drive straight down the ground which deserved four. Rampaul makes excellent ground from long-off and dives to save four
drops this down to the off side to bring up a fine half-century
gives himself a touch of room outside leg before smacking it through cover
flicked over midwicket
driven down to mid-off
full and straight, Shah sweeps but gets a top edge to the wicketkeeper who holds on to a simple chance
an ugly smudge down to fine-leg to get off the mark
squeezed out to point
immediately he opts for a slower ball on off stump which the batsman reads, defending it cautiously
a good bouncer, nice and quick - if not quite straight enough - but it keeps him on the back foot
too short - a bouncer, far too high and no-balled for height
solidly defended back to the bowler
flicked through midwicket
a firm punch out to deep extra cover
swept across the line. The shot goes nowhere
nudged to leg for another zero
punched down to long-on
another pointless chip for a couple through midwicket
square-driven out to deep backward point. Rampaul is again quick around the boundary edge to save four
punched to long-on
turned off his toes to midwicket and excellent running brings them two
this rather stops on the batsman, the ball spitting up off his bat out to no-man's land in the off side
an inside edge into his pads - Bravo shrieks an appeal but it's clear he got an inside edge
driven down the ground
a bouncer which he leaves alone
a touch too straight from Bravo, Mascarenhas works him to leg for a single...oh but in fact, a lazy piece of fielding allows two
and the captain goes. Excellent delivery cutting back into Collingwood who went back to defend, but got a thick inside edge which cannoned into his stumps
a slow full toss which, even before it reaches Plunkett, Bravo reacts to - jumping up with excitement. Plunkett is less excited, bumping it to leg before Bravo leaps across to field
what a catch! It's a corker from Gayle, Mascarenhas driving this fuller delivery, gets a thick outside edge to Gayle at first slip who pokes out his left hand...and it sticks. That was motoring
Broad stands tall, very tall, and drives it out to cover
too quick for Broad who is rapped on the pads. Edwards sprints down to give him a bit of chirp
too short, too wide and rightly wided. That flew over Broad's head...whose hair brushes the clouds, as he's about 9ft 8in
squirted to leg. Broad is well back in his crease here
on middle stump and Broad just defends this
squirted out to cover
and it's on off stump, Plunkett showing the full face of the bat in this defensive prod
drops this down to fine-leg
Broad square drives calmly, no great power in the stroke and they pick up a single
Plunkett ignores this outside his off stump
guided off a thick outside edge to third man
quite a pleasant stroke from Broad, driving at this outside his off stump. But no intent, timing or power - a push
cut down to third man
good line from Edwards, just outside Plunkett's off stump who comes forward to defend. Streakily...

another good catch - a very fine, running catch indeed from Samuels. It was down the leg side, Plunkett flicked it - but it got high on him, the ball then ballooning meekly off the bat and Samuels came sprinting in from deep backward square leg to take a fine, low catch
ooh a quick one, outside off, and it's left alone
a classy punch off the back foot from Broad straight back past the bowler. "Yeah, yeah yeah" is the call
pushed out to cover
Monty receives massive applause for this calm prod outside off, in doing so getting off the mark
Broad stands tall and smudges it out to the off side. No power or timing
turned off his hip - too straight from Powell
a full toss which takes Broad by surprise, and it's pumped to cover
no feet movement from Broad who swings at this, edging it straight to Gayle at first slip
ooh and he leaves it alone...at the very last moment
solidly blocked out from the Montster
guided out to point
quick, fiery delivery but it's very well played by Panesar, ducking beneath it like the No. 5 he is not
driven out to cover but West Indies are electric today and they save two
left alone outside off
defended off the back foot
but the wrong line from Powell and it wobbles off Panesar's pads for a single
blocked out to off. A touch too short
wider of the crease, Anderson tries a Goweresque cover drive but misses
the biggest cheer of the day! Anderson steps to the off side and flicks for a single, the crowd roaring their delight in Anderson getting off the mark
full, straight and defended
ooh, he plays and misses outside off
vicious! A horrible bouncer which rises onto Anderson's right ear, but he plays it well, swaying out of the way. A misfield allows them through for two
quick! This is lively from Edwards, Anderson trying to flick it over the slips but misses
too short this time, and Anderson turns him to leg for a single
edged...but over the slips for four! Edwards is on his knees in frustration - it sailed way over the slips and down to third man
defended out to cover but it's a no-ball
driven out to cover
left alone outside off
firmly defended
pushed out to cover
just short of a length, clumped back to the bowler
pushed out to cover for a crowd-relieving single
and it's nudged out to cover
shot! Monty stands tall and drives this crisply down the ground
dropped outside off
driven just short of extra cover
left alone outside off
outside off stump and Panesar goes for a fish without making contact
angling into Panesar, who defends with a straight bat...he's looked better than some of the top order
fuller from Edwards and driven to mid off
and he's been swept with vast amounts of cheek to fine-leg
swept to that short fine-leg
rapped on the pads attempting another sweep, but he's well outside the line
beaten in the flight. "How was that?" inquires Gayle
driven, or something, nowhere
another failed reverse sweep
defended off the back foot
wrapped on the pads on leg stump, and the umpire raises his finger - and there's a series win for West Indies, full deserved
